  "prompt": "How can India repeal Article 370?",
  "response": "Article 370, which granted special autonomous status to Jammu and Kashmir, was abrogated on August 5, 2019, through a presidential order and subsequent legislation passed in the Indian Parliament. Here's how it was repealed:\n\n1. Presidential Order\n- President Ram Nath Kovind issued a constitutional order\n- This order effectively nullified Article 370's provisions\n\n2. Parliamentary Approval\n- Both Rajya Sabha and Lok Sabha approved the resolution\n- The Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) had a majority in both houses\n- The resolution passed with a significant majority\n\n3. Legal Procedure\n- The presidential order declared that all provisions of the Indian Constitution would apply to Jammu and Kashmir\n- The state was bifurcated into two union territories: Jammu & Kashmir and Ladakh\n\n4. Constitutional Mechanism\n- Used Article 367 to interpret and modify Article 370\n- Argued that the special status was temporary\n\n5. Political Context\n- BJP government under Prime Minister Narendra Modi led the initiative\n- Argued that the move would integrate Jammu and Kashmir more closely with India\n\nThe repeal was controversial and led to significant political and legal discussions, but it was implemented successfully through constitutional and parliamentary procedures.",
